properties.areaDesc: Outer waters from Santa Cruz Island to San Clemente Island to 60 NM offshore including San Nicolas and Santa Barbara Islands; Waters from Pt. Sal to Santa Cruz Island CA and westward 60 nm including San Miguel and Santa Rosa Islands
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 27 at 9:15AM PST until January 29 at 9:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts to 35 kt and
combined seas 8 to 12 feet possible when conditions are worst.

* WHERE...Waters from Pt. Sal to San Clemente Island to 60 NM
offshore.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM PST Tuesday.
For the Gale Watch, from Tuesday evening through Wednesday
evening.

* IMPACTS...Potentially strong winds may create dangerous sea
conditions which could capsize or damage small and large
vessels.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...See the Coastal Waters Forecast (CWFLOX).
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and combined
seas.
